================================================================================
                   LOAN MODULE - ISSUES & IMPROVEMENTS TODO LIST
================================================================================
Last Updated: 18 Jun 2026
================================================================================

A. CRITICAL BUGS (Must Fix)
================================================================================

A1. [CRITICAL] Missing CSRF Token in AJAX Requests
   Files: Modules/Loan/resources/views/index.blade.php (lines 143-157, 175-191, 207-223, 237-253)
          Modules/Loan/resources/views/show.blade.php (lines 306-321, 339-354, 371-386)
   Issue: All AJAX POST/DELETE calls (loanApprove, loanReject, loanDisburse, loanDelete)
          do not include the _token parameter in the request data. Laravel's VerifyCsrfToken
          middleware will reject these requests with a 419 status error.
   Fix: Add `_token: "{{ csrf_token() }}"` to the data object in each AJAX call.



A3. [CRITICAL] No Employee Authorization on Loan Creation
   File: Modules/Loan/app/Http/Controllers/LoanController.php (lines 57-80)
   Issue: The store() method validates employee_id exists but does NOT verify it belongs
          to the authenticated user. A user could submit a loan for any employee.
          Also, the hidden input in create.blade.php can be manipulated via browser tools.
   Fix: Force employee_id to auth()->user()->employee->id instead of accepting from request.

A4. [CRITICAL] Loan Number Generation Is Fragile
   File: Modules/Loan/app/Services/LoanService.php (lines 149-157)
   Issue: Uses substr($lastLoan->loan_number, -4) to extract sequence number. This assumes
          the loan number always ends with exactly 4 digits (e.g., LN-2026-0001). If sequence
          exceeds 9999 → LN-2026-10000, substr returns "0000" instead of "10000", causing
          duplicate loan numbers and unique constraint violations.
   Fix: Use preg_match('/LN-\d{4}-(\d+)/', ...) to extract the numeric sequence properly,
        or explode by '-' and cast the last segment to int.

A5. [CRITICAL] Installments Never Marked As Overdue
   File: Modules/Loan/app/Models/LoanInstallment.php (scope exists but no auto-marking)
   Issue: Installments past their due_date remain in 'Pending' status. There is no
          scheduled job (artisan command) or logic that automatically marks past-due
          installments as 'Overdue'. Payroll deduction queries rely on this status.
   Fix: Create an artisan command (e.g., loan:check-overdue) to update installments
        where due_date < now() AND status = 'Pending' → 'Overdue'. Schedule via cron.

================================================================================

B. FUNCTIONAL ISSUES
================================================================================

B1. [HIGH] No Authorization/Policies for Loan Actions
   Files: Modules/Loan/app/Services/LoanService.php (approveLoan, rejectLoan, disburseLoan)
   Issue: Any authenticated user can call approve/reject/disburse endpoints. There is no
          role/permission check to ensure only authorized personnel (e.g., HR/Admin) can
          perform these actions. The approveLoan method uses auth()->id() without verification.
   Fix: Implement Laravel Policies or Gate checks (e.g., $user->can('approve-loan')).

B2. [HIGH] Floating Point Rounding Inconsistencies in Summary
   File: Modules/Loan/app/Services/LoanService.php (lines 351-368)
   Issue: The getLoanById() summary calculates totals from individual installments, which
          may differ slightly from loan's total_payable due to floating point rounding
          (e.g., 1000 / 3 = 333.333..., rounded to 333.33, 3 × 333.33 = 999.99 ≠ 1000.00).
   Fix: The last installment should absorb the rounding difference (e.g., last installment
        = total_payable - sum(previous_installments)).

B3. [HIGH] Remaining Amount Not Updated After Loan Disbursement
   File: Modules/Loan/app/Services/LoanService.php (lines 291-314)
   Issue: disburseLoan() updates status to 'Disbursed' but does NOT update remaining_amount.
          remaining_amount was set to total_payable during creation and never adjusted.
   Fix: Ensure remaining_amount = total_payable after disbursement (recalculate to be safe).

B4. [MEDIUM] SaveLoan On Update Destroys Installment Integrity
   File: Modules/Loan/app/Services/LoanService.php (lines 169-176)
   Issue: If an approved/disbursed loan could somehow be edited (guarded by status check),
          but the update doesn't handle existing installment records. If interest/amount
          changes, generated installments become invalid.
   Fix: On update of already-approved loans, warn user or force deletion/recreation of
        installment schedule.

B5. [MEDIUM] Variable $loan_id Not Passed For Update In saveLoan()
   File: Modules/Loan/app/Http/Controllers/LoanController.php (line 132-133)
   Issue: $validated['loan_id'] = $id is set but interest_rate is also set after, and
          the method unsets $data['loan_id'] inside saveLoan() using unset($data['loan_id']).
          This is redundant but not necessarily broken.
   Fix: Either pass loan_id as separate parameter or use proper update pathway.

================================================================================

C. ROUTING / URL STRUCTURE ISSUES
================================================================================

C1. [MEDIUM] Potential Route Collision: loans/dataTable vs loans/{id}/show
   File: Modules/Loan/routes/web.php (lines 9-10)
   Issue: If another route like loans/{id} (GET) were added, loans/dataTable could be
          interpreted as {id}=dataTable. Currently safe because specific routes are defined
          before any generic ones, but susceptible to future reordering.
   Recommendation: Keep routes in correct order. Consider prefixing admin routes:
        Route::prefix('admin')->group(...) or use explicit route names.

