D. VIEW / UI ISSUES
================================================================================

D1. [MEDIUM] Unused Variable In my.blade.php
   File: Modules/Loan/resources/views/my.blade.php
   File: Modules/Loan/app/Http/Controllers/LoanController.php (line 229)
   Issue: The myLoans() method passes both $employee and $loanSummary to the view,
          but my.blade.php only uses $loanSummary. $employee is never rendered.
   Fix: Remove $employee from compact() in controller.

D2. [MEDIUM] No Edit View Exists
   File: Modules/Loan/app/Http/Controllers/LoanController.php (line 114)
   Issue: edit() method references 'loan::edit' view but no edit.blade.php file exists
          in Modules/Loan/resources/views/. This will throw a ViewNotFoundException.
   Fix: Create edit.blade.php view or redirect show page with edit capabilities.

D3. [MEDIUM] No Loading/Disabled State on Action Buttons
   Files: All views
   Issue: Action buttons (Approve, Reject, Disburse, Delete) have no disabled state during
          AJAX calls. Users can click multiple times, triggering duplicate requests.
   Fix: Disable button and show spinner during AJAX call using beforeSend/complete.

D4. [LOW] Missing Loan Type Column in My Loans DataTable
   File: Modules/Loan/resources/views/my.blade.php (line 42)
   File: Modules/Loan/app/Services/LoanService.php (lines 107-144)
   Issue: The my-loans DataTable shows 'loan_type' as plain text without the colored badge
          that the admin DataTable has. Inconsistent UX.
   Fix: Add same loan_type badge rendering in getMyLoanDataTable().

================================================================================

E. DATABASE / MIGRATION ISSUES
================================================================================

E1. [MEDIUM] Existing Rows Missing loan_number
   File: Modules/Loan/Database/Migrations/2026_06_17_000003_add_loan_number_to_loans_table.php
   Issue: The migration adds loan_number column but does NOT backfill existing rows.
          All pre-existing loans will have NULL loan_number, which violates the unique
          constraint (MySQL treats NULLs as distinct, but application expects values).
   Fix: Add a backfill query in the migration:
        DB::statement("UPDATE loans SET loan_number = CONCAT('LN-', YEAR(created_at), '-', LPAD(id, 4, '0')) WHERE loan_number IS NULL");

E2. [LOW] try-catch Suppression of SQL Errors
   File: Modules/Loan/Database/Migrations/2026_06_17_000003_add_loan_number_to_loans_table.php
   Issue: Using empty try-catch blocks to suppress duplicate index errors makes debugging
          difficult. Better to use Schema::hasIndex() or conditional checks.
   Fix: Ideally use if (!Schema::hasIndex(...)) or catch specific exception types.

