F. PERFORMANCE / CODE QUALITY
================================================================================

F1. [MEDIUM] N+1 Query In getEmployeeLoanSummary()
   File: Modules/Loan/app/Services/LoanService.php (lines 507-525)
   Issue: getEmployeeLoanSummary() calls sum() on collection after loading all records.
          For employees with many loans, this loads unnecessary data into memory.
   Fix: Use aggregate queries: Loan::where(...)->sum('remaining_amount') etc.

F2. [LOW] Hardcoded Status Strings Throughout Code
   Files: Multiple
   Issue: Status values ('Pending', 'Approved', 'Rejected', 'Disbursed', 'Completed',
          'Cancelled') are hardcoded as strings in many places (controllers, services,
          views). Typo risk (e.g., 'Cancelled' vs 'Canceled').
   Fix: Define constants in the Loan model (e.g., STATUS_PENDING = 'Pending') and use
        Loan::STATUS_PENDING throughout.

F3. [LOW] Missing return type declarations
   Files: All PHP files
   Issue: Many methods lack proper return type hints (e.g., array, Collection).
   Fix: Add return types for better IDE support and code clarity.

